🌟 1D Array Basics – 10 C Programs
🔸 "Mastering the basics is the first step to becoming a pro!"

🔹 01. Program to Declare and Display Size of an Array
🔹 Question: Write a program to declare an array and display its size using sizeof.
🔹 Program:

#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int arr[10];
    int size = sizeof(arr) / sizeof(arr[0]);
    printf("Size of the array is: %d\n", size);
    return 0;
}
🔹 Sample Output:
Size of the array is: 10




🔹 02. Program to Take Input for an Array from the User
🔹 Question:Write a program to input elements in an array from the user.
🔹 Program:

#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int arr[5];
    printf("Enter 5 elements:\n");
    for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
        scanf("%d", &arr[i]);
    }
    printf("Elements stored successfully.\n");
    return 0;
}
🔹 Sample Output:
Enter 5 elements:
1 2 3 4 5
Elements stored successfully.






🔹 03. Program to Print Elements of an Array
🔹 Question: Write a program to print elements of an array.
🔹 Program:

#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int arr[5] = {10, 20, 30, 40, 50};
    printf("Array elements are:\n");
    for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
        printf("%d ", arr[i]);
    }
    printf("\n");
    return 0;
}
🔹 Sample Output:

Array elements are:
10 20 30 40 50







🔹 04. Program to Take and Display n Array Elements
🔹 Question:Write a program to input n elements in an array and print them.
🔹 Program:

#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int arr[100], n;
    printf("Enter number of elements (max 100): ");
    scanf("%d", &n);
    printf("Enter %d elements:\n", n);
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        scanf("%d", &arr[i]);
    }
    printf("Array elements are:\n");
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        printf("%d ", arr[i]);
    }
    printf("\n");
    return 0;
}
🔹 Sample Output:
Enter number of elements (max 100): 4
Enter 4 elements:
12 23 34 45
Array elements are:
12 23 34 45
